<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="734">
Etymology l 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182066" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole polita Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole polita Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">polita</taxonomicName>
, smooth, polished.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="734">
Diagnosis A shiny, reddish or brownish yellow member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
group, somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33606" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole balzani Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole balzani Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balzani">balzani</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33734" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fabricator (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fabricator (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabricator">fabricator</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182060" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole nigella Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole nigella Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigella">nigella</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
but immediately distinguishable from these and other species in the group by the following traits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="734">
Major and minor: body mostly smooth and shiny, reddish brown; humeri very prominently angulate, in major seen from above extending well beyond the lower sides of the pronotum; hind tibiae greatly swollen. Major: occipital border in full-face view very broadly and moderately concave. Measurements (mm) Major (
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182066" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole polita Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole polita Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">polita</taxonomicName>
lectotype): HW 1.20, HL 1.20, SL 0.62, EL 0.12, PW 0.62. Minor (
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182066" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole polita Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole polita Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">polita</taxonomicName>
paralectotype): HW 0.64, HL 0.66, SL 0.60, EL 0.08, PW 0.40.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="734">
Color Major (
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182066" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole polita Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole polita Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">polita</taxonomicName>
lectotype): body brownish yellow, appendages dark yellow (
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34098" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole wheeleri Mann" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole wheeleri Mann" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wheeleri">wheeleri</taxonomicName>
types are medium to light reddish brown, appendages a lighter shade of reddish brown).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="734">
Minor: concolorous yellowish brown (
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34098" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole wheeleri Mann" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole wheeleri Mann" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wheeleri">wheeleri</taxonomicName>
types have body medium reddish brown, appendages yellowish to reddish brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="734">
Range Rio Beni, Bolivia (
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182066" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole polita Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole polita Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">polita</taxonomicName>
types); Rio Madeira, Rondonia, Brazil (
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34098" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole wheeleri Mann" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole wheeleri Mann" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="734" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wheeleri">wheeleri</taxonomicName>
types); and Cuzco Amazonico, near Puerto Maldonado, Madre de Dios, Peru.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="734">biology At Cuzco Amazonico, Peru, Stefan Cover and John E. Tobin found a dense population of this species in a large clearing filled with logging detritus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
